It all depends how it owuld look like. I don't see the need of an economy. We are doing fine. We are also a commune, we share amny things, why can't we just be happy and do things for free. Then again, the free capitalist market is guarenteed by constitution.<br>
<br>
I'd like to see a detailed overview before I make up my mind.<br>
<br>
I'd like a socialized economy. <br>
In brief, we have X citizens. Each citizen needs foods, spices, beverages, luxuries and parfumes. If not all that can be grown on Menelmacari soil we will ahve to import. Our surplus of our own products can be exported. <br>
<br>
Caras Menelmacar is a gigantic city complex by Sirithil Straights. We need boats to go there from Haradwaith and Jaiha (main lands). Boats would also need to go to Edhilond and Tol Eressëa, since I believe flights would not be very good if we flew over the OAM.<br>
<br>
The military (REC) would need their share of the money, so tehy can keep our boys and girls in the army in good condition and health. Food and equipment is the essential there.<br>
<br>
The Culture and Education would need money too. The Library and Story telling for maintainance. The RPS, since they are significant for the culture. <br>
<br>
An economy would mean very much if we have a simulated one (that i'd accept), but a nonsimulated one as Hanover I do not really like. But that's just me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>-The currency name will be decided at a later time</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
It was called Menelmacari credit<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>-Hoefensfill will be the Economics Minister</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Menelmacar does not have any ministers at all. Perhaps <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>if</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> we have an economy, you could be Bank Governor.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>-The economy will join Sander's PhpMicroXChange project</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
If we have economy, yes, that'd be good.<br>
<br>
