<br>
Yeah sorry.<br>
<br>
Well you seem to want an economy based on simulated goods(entertainment)? But we have plenty of places where we could integrate a real-ish economy. I think over everything we should have a free economy. We are a very free micronation and too many restrictions wouldn't be good. Any kind of baracaon-type economy will require restrictions. Should we really base the economy on forced &quot;I build a factory&quot;? I mean ofcourse we could, but it would be harder to keep an active or semi-active economy because after a while building 20,000 chickens will get boring...<br>
<br>
Remember one thing, either you see all economies as simulated or all as real. There is really no difference in economic terms between Hanover's and the type you call &quot;simulated&quot; economy. Both can generate demand, and both have supply. Just that your type needs lots of rules and most products are &quot;imagined&quot;. In my opinion we should have a free economy so it will in essense be a mixed economy. But what will be produced will not be dictated by legislation but by supple and demand. I'm sure many people will have fun with simulated goods(and that makes them REAL goods but for entertainment.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm47.showPrevMessage?topicID=18.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm47.showNextMessage?topicID=18.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm47.emailToFriend?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm47.threadControl?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm47.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm47.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving e